President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate three individuals for various judicial positions. Charles Edward Atchley, Jr. is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Tennessee. He is currently an Assistant United States Attorney and has been the First Assistant United States Attorney since 2018. Katherine A. Crytzer is nominated to serve as Judge on the United States District Court for the Eastern District of Tennessee. She currently serves as Principal Deputy Assistant Attorney General at the Department of Justice's Office of Legal Policy. Sharon Goodie is nominated to serve as Associate Judge on the Superior Court of the District of Columbia. She is currently an Administrative Law Judge at the District of Columbia Office of Administrative Hearings.